HONG KONG, April 5 (Reuters Breakingviews) - In “America Second”, Isaac Stone Fish lays into executives who suck up to Beijing. He and Pete Sweeney discuss how politics and economics are forcing U.S. companies to reframe their approach, what legislations might be in the pipeline, and whether military conflict is inevitable.  Listen to the podcast (The host is a Reuters Breakingviews columnist. The opinions expressed are his own.) Follow @petesweeneypro on Twitter Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.